-- Brazil Coffee Exports Fall 4.3% in February, Ministry Says
-- B y   R o d r i g o   O r i h u e l a
-- 2012-03-01T19:59:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/brazil-coffee-exports-fall-4-3-in-february-ministry-says.html
Coffee exports from  Brazil , the
world’s largest producer and exporter, declined 4.3 percent in
February from a year earlier, Brazil’s Trade Ministry said.  Exports fell to 1.99 million bags from 2.08 million bags a
year earlier, the ministry said today in a report on its
website. A bag of coffee weighs 60 kilograms.  -- Editor: Adriana Brasileiro  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rodrigo Orihuela in Rio de Janeiro at 
